The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms and their performance bounds, which are commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions Contextual Bandits, which are a type of multi-armed bandit problem, and Markov Decision Processes, which are commonly studied in the robotics (cs.RO) and decision making (cs.DS) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.DS, cs.MA, and cs.RO.
